---
import PortalLayout from "../layouts/PortalLayout.astro";
---

<PortalLayout title="Playbook">
  <div class="max-w-4xl">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-2">Playbook</h1>
    <p class="text-stone-600 mb-8">Architecture, workflows, and standards for every site we build</p>

    <div class="space-y-8">

      <!-- Full Stack -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Full Stack</h2>
        <ol class="space-y-3">
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">1.</span>
            <div><strong>Claude (<a href="https://claude.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">claude.ai</a>)</strong> — conversational updates and builds</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">2.</span>
            <div><strong>Astro + Tailwind CSS</strong> — pages and styling</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">3.</span>
            <div><strong>GitHub (<a href="https://github.com/Spirit-Media-US" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">Spirit-Media-US</a>)</strong> — code only, never media</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">4.</span>
            <div><strong>Netlify</strong> — hosting, auto-deploys on push to <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">main</code></div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">5.</span>
            <div><strong>Cloudflare</strong> — domain, SSL, CDN, security</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">6.</span>
            <div><strong>Cloudflare R2</strong> — all images, audio, video</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">7.</span>
            <div><strong>Sanity (<a href="https://sanity.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">sanity.io</a>)</strong> — CMS for client content editing and media management with auto-optimization (MCP connected)</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">8.</span>
            <div><strong>GoHighLevel</strong> — CRM &amp; forms for internal sites, tagged by ministry (MCP connected)</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">9.</span>
            <div><strong>Google Docs MCP</strong> — documents, proposals, reports, content drafts</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">10.</span>
            <div><strong>Stitch</strong> (Google Stitch 2.0) — AI-powered design, generates pages and design systems (MCP connected)</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">11.</span>
            <div><strong>Playwright</strong> — browser testing, screenshots, cross-browser QA (MCP connected)</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">12.</span>
            <div><strong>UptimeRobot</strong> — uptime monitoring (every 5 min, all sites)</div>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <!-- Website Migration Protocol -->
      <section class="bg-rose-50 border border-rose-200 rounded-2xl p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-rose-700 mb-1">Website Migration Protocol</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm mb-1">Client-facing name: <strong>The Transformation System</strong> &nbsp;·&nbsp; Pipeline type: <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">migration</code></p>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-5">Clone an existing client website to the SMP stack. 9 phases — Claude does the work, you verify at checkpoints.</p>

        <!-- How to run a migration -->
        <div class="bg-white border border-rose-200 rounded-lg p-5 mb-6">
          <p class="font-bold text-rose-800 text-sm mb-3">How to run a migration</p>
          <ol class="list-decimal ml-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-600">
            <li><strong>SSH into Bethel as yourself</strong> (not deploy) and start Claude:<br/>
              <code class="bg-white border border-stone-200 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-mono mt-1 inline-block">cd ~/Sites && claude</code></li>
            <li>Say: <code class="bg-rose-100 border border-rose-200 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-mono">"Start migration for [Site Name] — slug: [slug], client URL: https://..."</code><br/>
              <span class="text-xs text-stone-500">Claude creates GitHub repo, Sanity project, Netlify site, and scaffold.</span></li>
            <li>When Phase 1 completes, move into the site directory:<br/>
              <code class="bg-white border border-stone-200 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-mono mt-1 inline-block">cd ~/Sites/&lt;slug&gt; && claude</code></li>
            <li>Say <strong>"continue migration"</strong> — Claude reads the protocol, checks which phase you're on, and starts working.</li>
            <li>Claude pauses at checkpoints. It pushes to dev and gives you the Netlify preview URL. Open it, compare against the original site.</li>
            <li>Say <strong>"continue"</strong> — Claude advances to the next phase and keeps working.</li>
            <li>If a session ends, start a new one and say <strong>"continue migration"</strong> again. It picks up where it left off.</li>
          </ol>
          <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mt-3">Phases are enforced in order. All work is attributed to your account. See <a href="/pipelines" class="text-rose-700 hover:underline">Pipelines</a> for the full command reference and shared tools.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Media rules -->
        <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6">
          <p class="font-bold text-amber-800 text-sm mb-2">Media rules — no exceptions</p>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-3 text-xs">
            <div><strong class="text-stone-700">Images</strong><br/><span class="text-stone-500">Sanity CMS. Auto-optimized CDN. Never in Git.</span></div>
            <div><strong class="text-stone-700">Audio</strong><br/><span class="text-stone-500">Cloudflare R2. Manual upload.</span></div>
            <div><strong class="text-stone-700">Video</strong><br/><span class="text-stone-500">YouTube iframe embed. Never &lt;video&gt; tag.</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- The 9 Phases -->
        <div class="space-y-6">

          <!-- Phase 1 -->
          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-rose-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">1</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">Infrastructure</p>
              <span class="text-xs font-bold text-rose-700 bg-rose-100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">AUTOMATED</span>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-2 text-xs text-stone-600">
              <p><strong>Claude does:</strong> Creates GitHub repo, Netlify site, Sanity project. Clones to Bethel. Sets up Astro 5 + Tailwind v4 scaffold, CLAUDE.md, .gitignore, dev branch.</p>
              <p><strong>You check:</strong> The pipeline dashboard shows links to GitHub, Netlify, and Sanity. Verify they exist.</p>
              <p><strong>Advances automatically</strong> when infrastructure is created.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Phase 2 -->
          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-rose-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">2</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">Content + CSS Extraction</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-2 text-xs text-stone-600">
              <p><strong>Claude does:</strong> Uses Playwright to crawl the original site at desktop (1280px) and mobile (375px). Extracts all content per page, complete computed CSS (colors, fonts, sizes, spacing, shadows, transitions), navigation structure, and catalogs all images with Sanity/R2 destinations.</p>
              <p><strong>Output files</strong> (in <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">content/</code>):</p>
              <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-2">
                <span class="bg-stone-50 rounded p-1.5 font-mono">site-inventory.md</span>
                <span class="bg-stone-50 rounded p-1.5 font-mono">design-tokens.md</span>
                <span class="bg-stone-50 rounded p-1.5 font-mono">images.md</span>
                <span class="bg-stone-50 rounded p-1.5 font-mono">pages/*.md</span>
              </div>
              <p><strong>You check:</strong> Claude tells you when extraction is done. Open <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">content/design-tokens.md</code> — verify it has Colors, Typography (desktop + mobile), Spacing (desktop + mobile), Decorations, and Navigation sections with real values. Check that page count in <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">pages/</code> matches <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">site-inventory.md</code>.</p>
              <p><strong>Say "continue"</strong> when verified.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Phase 3 -->
          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-rose-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">3</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">Design + Build</p>
              <span class="text-xs font-bold text-rose-600 bg-rose-50 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">Stitch MCP</span>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-2 text-xs text-stone-600">
              <p><strong>Claude does:</strong> Creates a Stitch project and design system from the extracted CSS tokens. Generates screens for every page (desktop + mobile) faithful to the original layout. Verifies designs match the original. Loads real fonts via Google Fonts. Writes <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">global.css</code> from design tokens (with mobile overrides) BEFORE building any pages. Builds all Astro pages using only CSS variables — no hardcoded hex values.</p>
              <p><strong>You check:</strong> Claude pushes to dev and runs "inspect dev preview". Check the Netlify preview URL and compare against the original site. Check: Do the colors match? Fonts? Spacing? Navigation? Does it look right on mobile?</p>
              <p><strong>Say "continue"</strong> when the site matches the original.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Phase 4 -->
          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-rose-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">4</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">Wire Sanity CMS</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-2 text-xs text-stone-600">
              <p><strong>Claude does:</strong> Uploads all images to Sanity. Defines schemas (blog posts, team, testimonials, events, FAQs &rarr; Sanity; legal pages, nav, footer &rarr; static). Migrates content into Sanity documents. Wires Astro pages to fetch from Sanity. Deploys schema. Sets up Sanity &rarr; Netlify webhook.</p>
              <div class="bg-rose-50 border border-rose-200 rounded p-2 mt-2">
                <p class="text-xs"><strong>Pipeline tool:</strong> If the site needs a blog, use the <a href="/pipelines#shared-tools" class="text-rose-700 hover:underline font-semibold">Blog Protocol</a> in your Claude session — Claude builds the full blog (search, categories, pagination, share bar, SEO) from a single command.</p>
              </div>
              <p><strong>You check:</strong> Preview the site — are all images loading from Sanity CDN? Open Sanity Studio — do all schemas and documents look right? Edit a document in Sanity — does the change appear on the site?</p>
              <p><strong>Say "continue"</strong> when CMS is wired and working.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Phase 5 — THE GATE -->
          <div class="border-2 border-rose-400 bg-white rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-rose-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">5</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-rose-800">CAR / Transformation Layer Report</p>
              <span class="text-xs font-bold text-white bg-rose-700 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">THE GATE</span>
            </div>
            <p class="text-rose-700 text-xs font-semibold mb-3 ml-10">Nothing past Phase 5 until all critical fixes are resolved.</p>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-2 text-xs text-stone-600">
              <p><strong>Claude does:</strong> Runs Migration Fidelity checklist (page count, nav, CTAs, footer, images, forms, side-by-side spot check). Generates Transformation Layer Report as a Google Doc with three parts:</p>
              <ul class="ml-4 space-y-1 text-stone-500">
                <li>&bull; <strong>Part One:</strong> Already Delivered — what's built and working</li>
                <li>&bull; <strong>Part Two:</strong> Critical Fixes — must fix before launch</li>
                <li>&bull; <strong>Part Three:</strong> Recommended Improvements — optional enhancements for Phase 6</li>
              </ul>
              <p>Claude then implements ALL critical fixes from Part Two.</p>
              <div class="bg-rose-50 border border-rose-200 rounded p-2 mt-2">
                <p class="text-xs"><strong>Pipeline tool:</strong> Run <a href="/pipelines#shared-tools" class="text-rose-700 hover:underline font-semibold">Pre-Launch QA</a> in your Claude session to generate the 8-scan report (Google Doc).</p>
              </div>
              <p><strong>You check:</strong> Claude shows the report link and lists what was fixed. Review the report. Preview the site — are the critical fixes resolved?</p>
              <p><strong>Say "continue"</strong> when all criticals are fixed.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Phase 6 -->
          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-rose-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">6</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">Design Refinement</p>
              <span class="text-xs font-bold text-rose-600 bg-rose-50 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">Stitch MCP</span>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-2 text-xs text-stone-600">
              <p><strong>Claude does:</strong> Takes the recommended improvements from CAR Part Three. Uses Stitch to generate design variants and refined screens. Picks the best variant and implements refinements in Astro. This is where the site goes from "faithful clone" to "better than the original."</p>
              <p><strong>You check:</strong> Preview the site. Does it look better than the original? Are the improvements from Part Three implemented? Check desktop and mobile.</p>
              <p><strong>Say "continue"</strong> when satisfied with the design.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Phase 7 -->
          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-rose-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">7</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">QA</p>
              <span class="text-xs font-bold text-rose-700 bg-rose-100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">AUTOMATED + MANUAL</span>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-2 text-xs text-stone-600">
              <p><strong>Claude does:</strong> Runs manual QA: Lighthouse audit, cross-browser testing (Playwright on Safari/Chrome/Firefox), form testing end-to-end, console error check, mobile responsiveness. Fixes everything found.</p>
              <div class="bg-rose-50 border border-rose-200 rounded p-2 mt-2">
                <p class="text-xs"><strong>Pipeline tool:</strong> Run <a href="/pipelines#shared-tools" class="text-rose-700 hover:underline font-semibold">Pre-Launch QA</a> in your Claude session. All 8 scans must pass. Re-run after fixes until clean.</p>
              </div>
              <p><strong>You check:</strong> Claude shows Lighthouse scores. Pre-Launch QA report is clean.</p>
              <p><strong>Say "continue"</strong> when all checks pass.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Phase 8 -->
          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-rose-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">8</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">Launch</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-3 text-xs text-stone-600">
              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 mb-1">Pre-launch (before connecting domain)</p>
                <p>Claude merges dev to main, verifies Netlify preview loads correctly, confirms Sanity webhook works, prepares redirects.</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 mb-1">Connect domain</p>
                <p>Claude configures Netlify custom domain, Cloudflare DNS (CNAME, proxy orange), and verifies SSL on www + apex.</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 mb-1">Post-launch verification (after domain is live)</p>
                <p>Verifies: all pages load, forms work, GA4 fires, sitemap is in Search Console, UptimeRobot is active, Open Graph preview is correct, redirects work.</p>
                <div class="bg-rose-50 border border-rose-200 rounded p-2 mt-2 space-y-1">
                  <p class="text-xs"><strong>Pipeline tool:</strong> Run <a href="/pipelines#shared-tools" class="text-rose-700 hover:underline font-semibold">Post-Launch QA</a> on the live URL — generates a Google Doc report with Lighthouse scores and auto-fixes.</p>
                  <p class="text-xs"><strong>Pipeline tool:</strong> When Post-Launch QA passes, run <a href="/pipelines#shared-tools" class="text-rose-700 hover:underline font-semibold">Site Audit &amp; Optimization Report</a> — generates the client-ready Google Doc.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <p><strong>You check:</strong> Visit the live site. Does everything work? Check GA4 real-time view. Share the URL on social media — does the preview card look right?</p>
              <p><strong>Say "continue"</strong> when everything is live and verified.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Phase 9 -->
          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-rose-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">9</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">Client Delivery &amp; Roadmap</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-2 text-xs text-stone-600">
              <p><strong>Claude does:</strong> Generates the client delivery email and post-launch roadmap (Google Doc) with recommended improvements not included in the initial build. Invites the client as a member in Sanity Studio.</p>
              <p><strong>You do:</strong> Send the delivery email to the client.</p>
              <div class="mt-3">
                <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 mb-1">Delivery email template:</p>
                <div class="relative">
                  <div class="bg-stone-100 px-3 py-2 rounded text-xs text-stone-600 whitespace-pre-wrap leading-relaxed" id="delivery-email">Subject: Your website is live! — [Site Name]

Hi [Client Name],

Your new website is live at [domain]!

We've put together a guide to help you manage your site content on your own:
&rarr; https://portal.spiritmediapublishing.com/clients

To set up your team's content editing access, please reply with the name and email address for each person who should be able to edit. We'll send them a Sanity Studio invite with everything they need to get started.

For anything beyond content edits — new pages, design changes, forms, or technical work — just email us at hello@spiritmediapublishing.com.

Welcome aboard!
SMP Team</div>
                  <button class="copy-btn absolute top-2 right-2 px-3 py-1 bg-rose-50 hover:bg-rose-100 text-rose-700 rounded text-xs font-semibold font-sans" data-copy-target="delivery-email">Copy</button>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

        <!-- Tool Reference -->
        <div class="mt-8 pt-6 border-t border-rose-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-rose-700 mb-4">Tool Reference</h3>
          <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mb-4">Run these from your Claude session inside the site directory: <code class="bg-white border border-stone-200 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-mono">cd ~/Sites/&lt;slug&gt; && claude</code></p>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-4">
              <div class="flex items-start justify-between">
                <div>
                  <p class="font-bold text-stone-800 text-sm">Start Migration</p>
                  <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 mt-1">Creates GitHub repo, Sanity project, Netlify site, and scaffold. Run from <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">~/Sites</code>.</p>
                </div>
                <a href="https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1LiDlC_0SddKGXBpgAqlydUVWeLGdLZ2R?usp=drive_link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-xs font-semibold text-rose-700 hover:underline shrink-0 ml-4">Drive &rarr;</a>
              </div>
              <code class="block bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 px-3 py-2 rounded text-xs font-mono text-stone-700 mt-2">Start migration for [Site Name] — slug: [slug], client URL: https://...</code>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-4">
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800 text-sm">Continue Migration</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 mt-1">Resumes from the current phase. Claude checks progress and picks up where you left off.</p>
              <code class="block bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 px-3 py-2 rounded text-xs font-mono text-stone-700 mt-2">continue migration</code>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-4">
              <div class="flex items-start justify-between">
                <div>
                  <p class="font-bold text-stone-800 text-sm">Pre-Launch QA</p>
                  <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 mt-1">8 code scans + build gate. Generates a Google Doc report. Use at Phase 5 (The Gate) and Phase 7 (QA).</p>
                </div>
                <a href="https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1LiDlC_0SddKGXBpgAqlydUVWeLGdLZ2R?usp=drive_link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-xs font-semibold text-rose-700 hover:underline shrink-0 ml-4">Drive &rarr;</a>
              </div>
              <code class="block bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 px-3 py-2 rounded text-xs font-mono text-stone-700 mt-2">Run Pre-Launch QA</code>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-4">
              <div class="flex items-start justify-between">
                <div>
                  <p class="font-bold text-stone-800 text-sm">Post-Launch QA</p>
                  <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 mt-1">Lighthouse + SEO + accessibility on the live URL. Auto-fixes what it can. Use at Phase 8 (Launch).</p>
                </div>
                <a href="https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1igaRd2Ed_Bat--5EnX0TlaSyCLjmcSnL?usp=drive_link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-xs font-semibold text-rose-700 hover:underline shrink-0 ml-4">Drive &rarr;</a>
              </div>
              <code class="block bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 px-3 py-2 rounded text-xs font-mono text-stone-700 mt-2">Run Post-Launch QA on https://[domain]</code>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-4">
              <div class="flex items-start justify-between">
                <div>
                  <p class="font-bold text-stone-800 text-sm">Site Audit &amp; Optimization Report</p>
                  <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 mt-1">Client-ready Google Doc — performance, SEO, accessibility, recommendations. Run after Post-Launch QA passes.</p>
                </div>
                <a href="https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1ekM2jpMHWFLou0cF7vbZYH2sIKL8kaoV?usp=drive_link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-xs font-semibold text-rose-700 hover:underline shrink-0 ml-4">Drive &rarr;</a>
              </div>
              <code class="block bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 px-3 py-2 rounded text-xs font-mono text-stone-700 mt-2">Run Site Audit Report on https://[domain]</code>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-4">
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800 text-sm">Blog Protocol</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 mt-1">Adds a full blog — search, categories, pagination, related posts, share bar, SEO. Kevin customizes later.</p>
