      <!-- New Site Build Protocol -->
      <section class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-2xl p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-700 mb-1">SMP Build Protocol (New Sites)</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm mb-1">Client-facing name: <strong>The Build System</strong> &nbsp;·&nbsp; Pipeline type: <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">newsite</code></p>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-5">Build a brand new website from scratch. 9 phases — Claude does the work, you verify at checkpoints.</p>

        <!-- How to run -->
        <div class="bg-white border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-5 mb-6">
          <p class="font-bold text-blue-800 text-sm mb-3">How to run a new site build</p>
          <ol class="list-decimal ml-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-600">
            <li><strong>SSH into Bethel as yourself</strong> (not deploy) and start Claude:<br/>
              <code class="bg-white border border-stone-200 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-mono mt-1 inline-block">cd ~/Sites && claude</code></li>
            <li>Say: <code class="bg-blue-100 border border-blue-200 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-mono">"Start new site build for [Site Name] — slug: [slug]"</code><br/>
              <span class="text-xs text-stone-500">Claude creates GitHub repo, Sanity project, Netlify site, and scaffold.</span></li>
            <li>When infrastructure is ready, move into the site directory:<br/>
              <code class="bg-white border border-stone-200 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-mono mt-1 inline-block">cd ~/Sites/&lt;slug&gt; && claude</code></li>
            <li>Say <strong>"continue newsite"</strong> — Claude starts Phase 1 (Discovery &amp; Brand).</li>
            <li>Claude pauses at checkpoints. It gives you the preview URL.</li>
            <li>Say <strong>"continue"</strong> — Claude advances to the next phase.</li>
            <li>If a session ends, start a new one and say <strong>"continue newsite"</strong>.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <!-- The 9 Phases -->
        <div class="space-y-6">

          <!-- Phase 1 -->
          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-blue-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">1</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">Discovery &amp; Brand</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-2 text-xs text-stone-600">
              <p><strong>Claude does:</strong> Researches the client — crawls social media, Google Business, any web presence. Extracts brand voice, colors, fonts, audience signals. Generates a creative brief as a Google Doc with: color palette (hex), font recommendations, sitemap, content outline per page.</p>
              <p><strong>You check:</strong> Claude shows the brief link. Review it — does the sitemap cover all needed pages? Does the brand direction feel right?</p>
              <p><strong>Say "continue"</strong> when the brief is good.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Phase 2 -->
          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-blue-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">2</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">Infrastructure</p>
              <span class="text-xs font-bold text-blue-700 bg-blue-100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">AUTOMATED</span>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-2 text-xs text-stone-600">
              <p><strong>Claude does:</strong> Bootstrap creates GitHub repo, Netlify site, Sanity project. Claude clones the repo, sets up Astro 5 + Tailwind v4 scaffold, creates CLAUDE.md and dev branch.</p>
              <p><strong>You check:</strong> GitHub, Netlify, and Sanity links work.</p>
              <p><strong>Advances automatically.</strong></p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Phase 3 -->
          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-blue-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">3</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">Design System</p>
              <span class="text-xs font-bold text-blue-600 bg-blue-50 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">Stitch MCP</span>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-2 text-xs text-stone-600">
              <p><strong>Claude does:</strong> Creates a Stitch project and design system from the creative brief (colors, fonts, roundness). Generates screens for every page (desktop + mobile). Applies the design system across all screens. Verifies designs match the brief.</p>
              <p><strong>You check:</strong> Claude shows the Stitch project. Do the designs match the brand direction from the brief?</p>
              <p><strong>Say "continue"</strong> when designs look right.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Phase 4 -->
          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-blue-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">4</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">Build Pages + Sanity</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-2 text-xs text-stone-600">
              <p><strong>Claude does:</strong> Loads real fonts (Google Fonts, not Stitch substitutes). Writes <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">global.css</code> from design tokens FIRST. Builds every page matching the Stitch designs — no hardcoded hex, all CSS variables. Wires Sanity CMS: defines schemas, uploads images, migrates content, sets up webhook.</p>
              <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded p-2 mt-2">
                <p class="text-xs"><strong>Pipeline tool:</strong> If the site needs a blog, use the <a href="/pipelines#shared-tools" class="text-blue-700 hover:underline font-semibold">Blog Protocol</a> in your Claude session — Claude builds the full blog from a single command.</p>
              </div>
              <p><strong>You check:</strong> Claude pushes to dev and runs "inspect dev preview". Check the Netlify preview — do pages look right? Edit a doc in Sanity Studio — does the change appear? <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">npm run build</code> succeeds?</p>
              <p><strong>Say "continue"</strong> when the site works.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Phase 5 — THE GATE -->
          <div class="border-2 border-blue-400 bg-white rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-blue-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">5</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-blue-800">CAR / Review Gate</p>
              <span class="text-xs font-bold text-white bg-blue-700 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">THE GATE</span>
            </div>
            <p class="text-blue-700 text-xs font-semibold mb-3 ml-10">Nothing past Phase 5 until all critical fixes are resolved.</p>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-2 text-xs text-stone-600">
              <p><strong>Claude does:</strong> Generates Transformation Layer Report (Google Doc) with Part One (delivered), Part Two (critical fixes), Part Three (improvements). Implements all critical fixes.</p>
              <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded p-2 mt-2">
                <p class="text-xs"><strong>Pipeline tool:</strong> Run <a href="/pipelines#shared-tools" class="text-blue-700 hover:underline font-semibold">Pre-Launch QA</a> in your Claude session to generate the 8-scan report (Google Doc). Re-run after fixes to confirm.</p>
              </div>
              <p><strong>You check:</strong> Claude shows report links. All 8 scans pass after fixes.</p>
              <p><strong>Say "continue"</strong> when all criticals are fixed.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Phase 6 -->
          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-blue-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">6</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">Design Polish</p>
              <span class="text-xs font-bold text-blue-600 bg-blue-50 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">Stitch MCP</span>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-2 text-xs text-stone-600">
              <p><strong>Claude does:</strong> Takes the recommended improvements from CAR Part Three. Uses Stitch to generate design variants, picks the best, implements refinements in Astro. Polishes spacing, responsiveness, micro-interactions.</p>
              <p><strong>You check:</strong> Preview the site. Does it look polished? Desktop + mobile?</p>
              <p><strong>Say "continue"</strong> when satisfied.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Phase 7 -->
          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-blue-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">7</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">QA</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-2 text-xs text-stone-600">
              <p><strong>Claude does:</strong> Runs manual QA: Lighthouse, cross-browser (Playwright), form testing, console errors, mobile responsiveness. Fixes everything found.</p>
              <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded p-2 mt-2">
                <p class="text-xs"><strong>Pipeline tool:</strong> Run <a href="/pipelines#shared-tools" class="text-blue-700 hover:underline font-semibold">Pre-Launch QA</a> in your Claude session. All 8 scans must pass. Re-run after fixes until clean.</p>
              </div>
              <p><strong>You check:</strong> Claude shows Lighthouse scores. Pre-Launch QA report is clean.</p>
              <p><strong>Say "continue"</strong> when all checks pass.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Phase 8 -->
          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-blue-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">8</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">Launch</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-2 text-xs text-stone-600">
              <p><strong>Claude does:</strong> Merges to main, verifies Netlify preview. Connects custom domain, Cloudflare DNS, SSL. Verifies: all pages load, forms work, GA4 fires, sitemap in Search Console, UptimeRobot active, Open Graph correct.</p>
              <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded p-2 mt-2 space-y-1">
                <p class="text-xs"><strong>Pipeline tool:</strong> Run <a href="/pipelines#shared-tools" class="text-blue-700 hover:underline font-semibold">Post-Launch QA</a> on the live URL — generates a Google Doc report with Lighthouse scores and auto-fixes.</p>
                <p class="text-xs"><strong>Pipeline tool:</strong> When Post-Launch QA passes, run <a href="/pipelines#shared-tools" class="text-blue-700 hover:underline font-semibold">Site Audit &amp; Optimization Report</a> — generates the client-ready Google Doc.</p>
              </div>
              <p><strong>You check:</strong> Visit the live site. Everything works? GA4 real-time shows traffic? Share URL on social — preview card looks right?</p>
              <p><strong>Say "continue"</strong> when everything is live.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Phase 9 -->
          <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-blue-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">9</div>
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">Client Delivery &amp; Roadmap</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-10 space-y-2 text-xs text-stone-600">
              <p><strong>Claude does:</strong> Generates the delivery email and post-launch roadmap (Google Doc). Invites client to Sanity Studio.</p>
              <p><strong>You do:</strong> Send the delivery email to the client.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

