      <!-- New Rules (March 2026) -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">New Rules <span class="text-sm font-normal text-stone-500">(March 2026)</span></h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-4">Mandatory rules established 2026-03-30. These apply to all sessions, all developers, and all sites.</p>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="bg-stone-50 border-l-4 border-red-700 px-4 py-3 rounded-r">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 text-sm mb-1">Mandatory cd-then-claude startup</p>
            <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Always <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">cd ~/Sites/(slug) && claude</code> before working on any site. Running Claude from <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">~/</code> or <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">~/Sites/</code> is blocked.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-stone-50 border-l-4 border-red-700 px-4 py-3 rounded-r">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 text-sm mb-1">Pre-edit hook enforcement</p>
            <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">A hook in <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">settings.json</code> blocks edits to site files when CWD is <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">~/</code> or <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">~/Sites/</code>. This prevents bypassing per-project CLAUDE.md rules.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-stone-50 border-l-4 border-red-700 px-4 py-3 rounded-r">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 text-sm mb-1">MailtoLink component standard</p>
            <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Every site must have a <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">MailtoLink</code> component. Bare <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">mailto:</code> links are banned.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-stone-50 border-l-4 border-red-700 px-4 py-3 rounded-r">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 text-sm mb-1">CSP headers required</p>
            <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Every site must have a <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">netlify.toml</code> with <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">[[headers]]</code> including <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">Content-Security-Policy</code>.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-stone-50 border-l-4 border-red-700 px-4 py-3 rounded-r">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 text-sm mb-1">Project-scoped Sanity tokens</p>
            <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Each Sanity project needs its own write token in <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">.secrets</code>. Do not share tokens across projects.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-stone-50 border-l-4 border-red-700 px-4 py-3 rounded-r">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 text-sm mb-1">New site auto-detection</p>
            <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">A cron job runs at 4 AM UTC, scans <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">~/Sites/</code>, and auto-adds new repos to the global CLAUDE.md.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

